				                    <h2 class="post__title">
                        <a href="https://www.theawl.com/2017/06/geri-allen-1957-2017/">Geri Allen, 1957 -- 2017</a>
                    </h2>

                    <div class="post__byline">
						by                        <span class="post__author">Alex Balk</span>
                    </div>
				
                <div class="post__body post__content">
					<div><h4>And now she’s dead.</h4>
<figure><img alt="" src="http://www.theawl.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/13xZd-1Kh30tahvhUGejErw.jpeg"><figcaption>Photo:<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/treyguinn/292228602/in/photolist-ak3kLE-rPKob-a3Tt5d-a3QCaP-a3QBYn-a3QC1e-a3QC8n-a3QC7t-a3Tt8q-86TQA9-a3QC9n-86QDTc-amHCoq-8jDEC6-86TQpf-a3Tt79-a3TsYE-86TQiU-86QDM2-a3Tt2S-86TQSy-86QDAT-86TQsL-LJYMEC-KR5gvX-a3Tt5W-86TQc7-86TQ9Y-rPMGQ-ajZyec-rPNWC-rPLuf-rPMnJ-rPNiQ-rPM6b-rPJvT-rPKC3-rPNAW-rPKUC-rPKa2-rPLMv-rPJSm-LEZEgg-KR5hMp-LJYPCf-Lmx5NU-LCrTQY-KR5hNg-8iPQni-rPL8R"> Trey Guinn</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>Geri Allen, “<a href="http://www.freep.com/story/entertainment/music/2017/06/28/geri-allen-dies-obituary-detroit-jazz/434339001/">widely considered by critics and her peers as one of the greatest contemporary jazz pianists</a>,” died yesterday in Philadelphia. She was 60. Here she is with Charlie Haden and Paul Motian from 1987’s<em> Etudes</em>.</p>
<p><iframe src="https://cdn.embedly.com/widgets/media.html?src=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FOzqLa5mWAJ0%3Ffeature%3Doembed&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DOzqLa5mWAJ0&amp;image=https%3A%2F%2Fi.ytimg.com%2Fvi%2FOzqLa5mWAJ0%2Fhqdefault.jpg&amp;key=a19fcc184b9711e1b4764040d3dc5c07&amp;type=text%2Fhtml&amp;schema=youtube" width="854" height="480" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"><a href="https://medium.com/media/5bc489b62037c9d3fa659dd69604922a/href">https://medium.com/media/5bc489b62037c9d3fa659dd69604922a/href</a></iframe></p>
</div>                </div>
            </div>
		
			
